modules.description: This module provides operations for HTTP request handling, including routing (path-based, regex, virtual hosts), middleware composition, rate limiting, and logging, alongside response generation for text, Gemini, and raw content. It works with HTTP requests/responses, routes, middleware pipelines, network addresses, file paths, and CGI scripts, supporting Unix filesystem interactions. Use cases include building scalable web applications with dynamic content via CGI execution, serving static files, and configuring Lwt-based HTTP servers with fine-grained access control and scoped route grouping.
